                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/72T0> ;
                                   rdfs:label "Morphological" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Morphological features describe geometric aspects of a region of interest (ROI), such as area and volume. Morphological features are based on ROI voxel representations of the volume." .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/HDEZ
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/HDEZ> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IPET> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "NGTDM_Complexity" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Complex textures are non-uniform and rapid changes in grey levels are common" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/HJ9O
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/HJ9O> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/TP0I> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "GLRLM_RunEntropy" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/HTZT
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/HTZT> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/TP0I> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "GLRLM_ShortRunLowGreyLevelEmphasis" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The SRLGLE measures the joint distribution of short runs and low gray level values. The SRLGE is high for the image with many short runs and lower gray level values" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/HW1V
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/HW1V> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/9SAK> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "GLSZM_SmallZoneHighGreyLevelEmphasis" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "This feature emphasises runs in the lower left quadrant of the GLSZM, where small zone sizes and high grey levels are located" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IAZD
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IAZD> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/1XL1> .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IB1Z
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IB1Z> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   owl:equivalentClass <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/26200> ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/LFYI> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "GLCM_InverseDifference" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Inverse difference is a measure of homogeneity. Grey level co-occurrences with a large difference in levels are weighed less, thus lowering the total feature score. The feature score is maximal if all grey levels are the same" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IC23
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IC23> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/TP0I> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "GLRLM_RunLengthNonUniformityNormalised" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "This is the normalised version of the run length non-uniformity feature" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IJAQ
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IJAQ> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/OWOH> .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IMOQ
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IMOQ> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/REK0> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "GLDM_HighDependenceEmphasis" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "This feature emphasises high neighbouring grey level dependence counts" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IPET
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IPET> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/ZOEY> ;
                                   rdfs:label "Neighbourhood Grey Tone Difference Matrix (NGTDM)" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The neighbourhood grey tone difference matrix (NGTDM) contains the sum of grey level differences of pixels/voxels with discretised grey level i and the average discretised grey level of neigh- bouring pixels/voxels within a distance d. See also https://doi.org/10.1109/21.44046" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IPH6
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IPH6> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/UHIW> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "Kurtosis" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Kurtosis is a measure of how outlier-prone a distribution is. The kurtosis of the normal distribution is 3. Distributions that are more outlier-prone than the normal distribution have kurtosis greater than 3; distributions that are less outlier-prone have kurtosis less than 3" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/IQYR
