                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/HCUG> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "LeastAxisLength" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The least axis is the the axis along which the object is least extended. The least axis is twice the semi-axis length, determined using the smallest eigenvalue obtained by PCA on the point set of voxel centers" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/7NFM
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/7NFM> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/LFYI> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "GLCM_ClusterShade" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The cluster shade is a measure of the skewness of the matrix and it is believed to gauge the perceptual concepts of uniformity. When the cluster age is high the image is asymmetric" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/7T7F
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/7T7F> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/HCUG> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "AreaDensityCH" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The area density convex hull is defined as the ratio between  the area and the surface of the convex hull obtained by summing the sum of the area of the faces in the convex hull" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/7TET
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/7TET> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/UHIW> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "CoefficientOfVariation" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Coefficient of variation is the ratio between the standard deviation and the mean value" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/72T0
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/72T0> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf :Biomarkers ;
                                   rdfs:label "Radiomics Features" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Radiomics features are particular features which can be extracted from objects within an image (e.g. from a region of interest) and that can potentially present a prognostic value (e.g related to the survival probability of a patient)." .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/8CE5
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/8CE5> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/TP0I> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "GLRLM_GreyLevelVariance" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "This feature estimates the variance in runs for the grey levels" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/8DWT
<http://www.radiomics.org/RO/8DWT> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf <http://www.radiomics.org/RO/UHIW> ;
                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy "IBSI" ;
                                   rdfs:label "Percentile90" ;
                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The statistical 90th percentile of the grey level distribution" .


###  http://www.radiomics.org/RO/8QU8
